    "course_title": "DIVERSITY IN SPECIAL EDUCATION",
    "description": "Provides an overview of the context and unique considerations for providing special education services to culturally and linguistically diverse learners and their families.  Upon completion, describe the diversity of students who receive special education services, including trends over time, and identify deficit orientations toward diversity, culture and disability that limit youths' opportunities to learn.",
